\begin{abstract}
We advocate the possibility that the scalar field that can address observed diphoton excess at $750$\,GeV at LHC is a part of the $SU(5)$ symmetry breaking sector. The field in question is the Standard Model singlet that resides in the adjoint representation that breaks $SU(5)$ down to $SU(3) \times SU(2) \times U(1)$. We also show that the required production and subsequent decay to two photons of this singlet, apart from already existing proposals, can be induced by the presence of a scalar leptoquark multiplet that transforms as $(\bm{3},\bm{2},7/6)$ under $SU(3) \times SU(2) \times U(1)$. 
\end{abstract}

